SampleID: Luminescence = Combination of different luminescence techniques (TL, OSL, and IRSL)
Calibrated 14C = Carbon-14 date calibrated with a radiocarbon calibration curve (usually IntCal or ShCal) to get a calendar year BP

Calibrated and modeled 14C = Carbon-14 date calibrated with a radiocarbon calibration curve (usually IntCal or ShCal) and then underwent Bayesian modeling in relation to other 14C dated layers at the site to get a calendar year BP
delta-18O shell = Oxygen-18 isotope ratios from shells matched to those of marine isotope stages (MIS)
SG-OSL = Single grain optically stimulated luminescence
MC-ICPMS = multi-collector-inductively coupled plasma mass spectrometry
LU ESR = Linear uptake model electron spin resonance

Stone ages (for southern Africa - mainly based on KRM):
Middle Stone Age I = 115,000 - 110,000 years ago (McCall 2006, Table 7: https://doi.org/10.1016/j.jhevol.2006.06.003)
Middle Stone Age II = 85,000 - 70,000 years ago (McCall 2006, Table 7: https://doi.org/10.1016/j.jhevol.2006.06.003)
Howiesons Poort (between MSA II and MSA II at KRM) = 80,000 - 65,000 years ago (McCall 2006, Table 7: https://doi.org/10.1016/j.jhevol.2006.06.003)
Middle Stone Age III/IV = 50,000 - 45,000 years ago (McCall 2006, Table 7: https://doi.org/10.1016/j.jhevol.2006.06.003)
